<HEAD>THE PLAIN DEALER. No 20.</HEAD>
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q> 
<L>Tum pater Anchi&s;es lachrymis ingre&s;&s;us obortis:</L> 
<L>O nate, ingentem luctum ne quaere tuorum:</L> 
<L>O&s;tendent terris hunc tantum fata, ne&abque; ultr&acirc;</L> 
<L>E&s;&s;e &s;inent &mdash;</L> 
<BIBL>VIR.</BIBL> </Q>
<Q> 
<L>Heu mi&s;erande puer! Si qua fata a&s;pera rumpas,</L> 
<L>Tu Marcellus eris. &mdash;</L> 
<BIBL>Ibid.</BIBL> </Q>
<Q> 
<L>Di&s;cite ju&s;titiam moniti, &amp; non temnere divos.</L> 
<BIBL>Ibid.</BIBL> </Q>
